Do you know how many iPods® Apple has to
                sell to support its stock price? 



Why is this important?
  
            We believe stock prices are a reflection of the common belief that management can
            deliver the performance to support the price of its stock. Therefore, for example,
            knowing how many iPods®, desktops, portables
            and iPhones® Apple has to sell to support
            the price of its stock and the likelihood that management can actually deliver this
            performance, we believe, is critical to making a good investment decision and is
            the basis of the Transparent Value investment methodology.
        


































