Armen Arus: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 28, 2017 9:53 PM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of Transparent Value Advisors, LLC



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Armen   Arus  Co-Chief Executive Officer and Senior Portfolio Manager, Transparent Value Advisors, LLCAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 0 Board Members in 0 different organizations across 6 different industries.----
Background

		Mr. Armen Arus serves as the Co-Chief Executive Officer and Senior Portfolio Manager of Transparent Value Advisors, LLC. Mr. Arus co-founded Transparent Value in 2003. He serves as the Co-Chief Executive Officer of Guggenheim Transparent Value, LLC and its subsidiaries, President of Transparent Value Trust, and a Managing Director of Guggenheim Investment Management, LLC. Mr. Arus directs Transparent Value’s product and corporate operations, and product development activities. ... He serves as Portfolio Manager of Transparent Value Trust - Transparent Value SMID Cap Directional Allocation Fund. He served as Portfolio Manager of Transparent Value Trust - Transparent Value Directional Allocation Fund and Transparent Value Trust - Transparent Value Small-Cap Fund. He contributed to the development of business strategy, investment processes, and distribution activities, and is responsible for developing the marketing strategy and plan. He served as Portfolio Manager of Transparent Value Trust - Transparent Value Dividend Fund, Transparent Value Trust - Transparent Value Large-Cap Value Fund, Transparent Value Trust - Transparent Value Large-Cap Growth Fund, Transparent Value Trust - Transparent Value Large-Cap Core Fund, Transparent Value Trust - Transparent Value Large-Cap Aggressive Fund, Transparent Value Trust - Transparent Value Large-Cap Defensive Fund and Transparent Value Trust - Transparent Value Large-Cap Market Fund. Mr. Arus has a vast experience in asset management, investment research and investment banking. He served as Portfolio Manager of Guggenheim Investment Management LLC and Transparent Value Trust - Transparent Value Directional Allocation VI Portfolio. Mr. Arus was employed at Financial Resource Group LLC, where he worked on all aspects of executing private equity, M&A, and bridge-financing transactions. From 1999 to 2000, he served as an Analyst at the Acquisition Finance group of Chase Securities, Inc., where he recommended capital structure and financing strategies to private equity clients and conducted qualitative and quantitative analyses for leveraged buyouts and M&A transactions. From 1996 to 1998, Mr. Arus worked at the Commercial Mortgage Backed Securities Group of Lehman Brothers Inc., where he was responsible for evaluating and analyzing real estate investment projects, and for building valuation models for mortgage-backed assets. He also performed sensitivity analyses to help model the hypothetical behavior of assets aggregated in securitized instruments. He holds BS in Finance from New York University - Leonard N. Stern School of Business.Read Full Background




