Transparent Value Trust - Guggenheim Directional Allocation Fund: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 28, 2017 9:53 PM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of Transparent Value Trust - Guggenheim Directional Allocation Fund



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Transparent Value Trust - Guggenheim Directional Allocation Fund is an open-ended equity indexed mutual fund launched and managed by Guggenheim Partners Investment Management LLC. It invests into the public equity markets of the United States. The fund invests in stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors, including REITs. It invests in stocks of large cap companies. The fund also invests in cash or cash equivalents. It seeks to replicate the performance of the Guggenheim Directional Allocation Index, by investing in stocks of companies as per their weightings in the index. The fund was formerly known as Transparent Value Trust - Transparent Value Directional Allocation Fund. T...
Transparent Value Trust - Guggenheim Directional Allocation Fund is an open-ended equity indexed mutual fund launched and managed by Guggenheim Partners Investment Management LLC. It invests into the public equity markets of the United States. The fund invests in stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors, including REITs. It invests in stocks of large cap companies. The fund also invests in cash or cash equivalents. It seeks to replicate the performance of the Guggenheim Directional Allocation Index, by investing in stocks of companies as per their weightings in the index. The fund was formerly known as Transparent Value Trust - Transparent Value Directional Allocation Fund. Transparent Value Trust - Guggenheim Directional Allocation Fund was formed on June 18, 2012 and is domiciled in the United States.
Detailed Description


100 Wilshire BoulevardSanta Monica, CA 90401United StatesFounded in 2012



